50|$|<b>Scabbards</b> were {{generally}} made from two plates of iron, and suspended from a belt made of iron links. Some <b>scabbards</b> had front plates of bronze rather than iron. This was more common on Insular examples than elsewhere; {{only a very}} few Continental examples are known.|$|R
