25|$|Sword belt: A sword belt is a {{belt with}} an {{attachment}} for the sword's <b>scabbard,</b> {{used to carry}} it when not in use. It is usually fixed to the <b>scabbard</b> of the sword, providing a fast means of drawing the sword in battle. Examples of sword belts include the Balteus used by the Roman legionary.|$|E
